  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Requests are key indicators of a project's health and status. Monitoring trends in the number of defects and&#xD;
    enhancement requests that arrive and are closed over time supports planning, estimation and risk management. Request&#xD;
    trends are also analyzed to determine the stakeholder's level of satisfaction with the solution. Unaddressed requests&#xD;
    can impact the stakeholders' perception of value.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Count in each unit of time (typically each iteration). Requests include defects and enhancement requests.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Total number of submitted change requests&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Total number of approved change requests&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Total number of resolved change requests&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Cumulative:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Total cumulative change requests found and closed.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A good way to monitor Change Request Trend is with a set of trend lines. Plot submitted change requests and closed&#xD;
    change requests on the Y axis and iterations on the X axis. Cumulative change requests found and closed are also&#xD;
    plotted on two trend lines. The difference between the two lines shows the change requests remaining.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A high number of change requests indicates that the system has been used. If the majority of change requests are&#xD;
    defects, there may be a problem with quality. If the majority of change requests are enhancement requests, the team may&#xD;
    not have delivered the right set of requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For specific analysis information view metrics: &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_metrics-ibm/guidances/supportingmaterials/defect_trends_2E2A9ABF.html&quot; guid=&quot;_AIQmoITEEd2AfZddKTmDRA&quot;>Defect Trends&lt;/a> and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.mgmt.common.extend_metrics-ibm/guidances/supportingmaterials/enhancement_request_trend_6560BA36.html&quot; guid=&quot;_vyouZpbmEd27uMM_wDtgBA&quot;>Enhancement Request Trend&lt;/a>.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
